https://www.reddit.com/r/cybersecurity/comments/1tp73x5/glassworm_takedown_yearlong_developer_supply/

My thoughts : Another supply chain compromise, this time attributed to GlassWorm. The malicious VSCode extensions are something that I'm still surprised there aren't tighter controls around- for instance I'm curious what measures are taken to scan/validate that newly added extensions don't contain malware as in this instance keyloggers were installed and exfiltrated crypto wallets, npm credentials, GitHub tokens, etc to GlassWork C2 infrastructure. Good to know that the C2 infra is down as of now but Microsoft's recalcitrance to take down the extensions or notify affected users of the malware is not a good sign. There must be more investigation happening internally.





